---
<SiteLayout site="28grams" title="Avocado Oil Guide" description="Avocado oil — smoke point myth, refined vs unrefined, worth the price?" canonical="https://28grams.vip/avocado-oil-guide" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero"><h1>Avocado Oil Guide</h1><p>Exploring the high-heat champion.</p></div>

    <h2>Smoke Point Reality</h2>
    <p>Avocado oil is famous for its exceptionally high smoke point, often cited around 520°F (270°C) for the refined version. Unrefined avocado oil has a lower smoke point but offers a distinct, buttery flavor.</p>
    <h2>Refined vs Unrefined</h2>
    <p>Refined avocado oil is ideal for high-heat searing and frying due to its neutral taste and stability. Unrefined avocado oil is better suited for dressings and lower-heat applications.</p>
    <h2>Is It Worth the Price?</h2>
    <p>Given its versatility and health benefits—rich in oleic acid and lutein—many find avocado oil worth the premium price, especially for specific cooking techniques that require high heat without imparting strong flavors.</p>
    <div class="card">
      <h3>Related Guides</h3>
      <p>Return to the <a href="/cooking-oils-compared">Main Cooking Oils Guide</a> or read about <a href="/olive-oil-guide">Olive Oil</a> and <a href="/coconut-oil-guide">Coconut Oil</a>.</p>
    </div>

  </div>
